Audit Event Logging

Files:

1. AuditEventMapping ==> com/ipvs/common/service/AuditEventMapping.xml
2. AuditEventLogger ==>  com/ipvs/common/service/AuditEventLogger.java
3. AuditEventUtils ==>  com/ipvs/common/service/AuditEventUtils.java
4. AuditEvent ==>  com/ipvs/common/service/AuditEvent.java
5. EventLoggerI ==> com/ipvs/common/service/EventLoggertI.java


 ==> LOGGING EVENT USING AUDITEVENTMAPPING FILE
      AuditEventMapping:  contains the event mapping  based on object and action or request name
	  ==> Adding Event Based on Object or action: 
		    1. Add entry in AuditEventMapping 
		         	<EventMapping action='ReplaceRequest' objectType='AssetResource' eventType='Device' eventName='Modify' targetXPath='//Info/Title' />
		    2. implements EventLoggerI in request handler 
		    3. Create AuditEvent object in getAuditEvent method using AuditEventUtils methods getAuditEventObjectBasedOnObjectAndAction 
		    
	  ==> Adding event Based on Request 
	       1. Add Entry in AuditEventMapping 
	                <EventMapping action='DeleteRequest' objectType='Device' eventType='Device' eventName='Delete' targetXPath='//Device/@title'>
						<RequestList>
							<Request>DeleteDeviceRequest</Request>
						</RequestList>
					</EventMapping>

Note: If the handler result doc does not contains the values then read/create document accordingly and set it in request loggerDocument.					

 ==> LOGGING EVENT USING EVENTLOGGERI IN REQUEST HANDLER
         1. implements EventLoggerI in request handler 
		 2. Create AuditEvent based on your requirement 

 ==> LOGGING EVENT AT AGENT LEVEL / CUSTOM EVENTS
        1. Create AuditEvent object based on Your Requirement
        2. Add auditEvent object to AuditEventLogger queue.
    	 
 ==> LOGGING EVENT FOR ASYN REQUESTS
        1. Create AuditEvent object in hanldeAgentResponse of AgetnResponseHanlder
        2. Pass Audit Event object to handleResponse of MRResponseHandlerI		

	 
		    				
		                       

 
                       
   